'''Shōichii''' ({{ill|Senior First Rank|ja|正一位|1=Senior First Rank|12=draft}}) is one of the highest [[Court ranks in Japan|ranks]] in Japan's system of {{ill|Ritsuryō|ja|律令制|12=draft}}-based hierarchy and [[Shinkai (divine rank)|Shinkai (divine ranks)]]. It ranks above {{ill|Junior First Rank|ja|従一位|1=Junior First Rank|12=draft}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-ranks/court-ranks/</ref>
== Overview == The rank of Shōichii has been historically conferred upon individuals who made extraordinary contributions to the state, such as {{ill|Kampaku|ja|関白|12=draft}}, {{ill|Daijō Daijin|ja|太政大臣|12=draft}}, or {{ill|Shogun|ja|征夷大将軍|12=draft}}. However, only seven individuals have ever received this rank during their lifetime.<ref group="注釈">These include {{ill|Fujiwara no Miyako|ja|藤原宮子|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fujiwara no Muchimaro|ja|藤原武智麻呂|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tachibana no Moroe|ja|橘諸兄|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro|ja|藤原仲麻呂|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fujiwara no Nagate|ja|藤原永手|12=draft}}, {{ill|Minamoto no Katako|ja|源方子|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Sanetomi Sanjō|ja|三条実美|12=draft}}. Two of these individuals, Fujiwara no Muchimaro and Sanetomi Sanjō, passed away on the same day they received the rank.</ref> Most instances of this rank were posthumously awarded as {{ill|Zōi|ja|贈位|12=draft}}.
After {{ill|Meiji Restoration|ja|明治維新|12=draft}}, the rank was formalized under the {{ill|Shokuinrei|ja|職員令|12=draft}} of 1869.<ref>{{Egov law|215IO0000000325|位階令}}</ref> However, the rank became symbolic as the role's corresponding duties ceased to exist.
For {{ill|Shinkai (divine rank)|lt=Shin’i|ja|神階|1=Shinkai (divine rank)|12=draft}}, many shrines achieved the rank of Shōichii over time, particularly with the {{ill|Inari shrines|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}}, which adopted this rank after the main shrine, {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|12=draft}}, received imperial recognition.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://inari.jp/about/history/num04/ |title=稲荷勧請 |publisher=伏見稲荷大社 |accessdate=2024-01-21}}</ref>
=== Shrines Awarded Shōichii === * {{ill|Kamo Shrine|ja|賀茂神社|12=draft}} – 807 AD * {{ill|Katori Shrine|ja|香取神宮|12=draft}} – 850 AD * {{ill|Kasuga Shrine|ja|春日神社|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kashima Shrine|ja|鹿島神宮|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hiyoshi Taisha|ja|日吉大社|12=draft}}
